benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/availableBasePlans - Retrieve available base plans

covered: Valid Request scenarios (TC01, TC02) cover typical successful retrieval with and without accountId
Empty Response scenarios (TC03, TC14) cover no-data cases
Query Parameters handling (TC02, TC04, TC05, TC08, TC12, TC13) tests invalid/edge inputs and parameter combinations
Authorization handling (TC06) covers unauthorized access with 401
System health and resilience scenarios (TC07 503, TC17 504) tested
Performance scenarios (TC09-11) cover under normal and peak loads
Security input validation (TC12-13) cover SQLi and XSS attempts
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested
Rate limiting/throttling behavior is not tested
Caching behavior headers (ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
Only 401 is tested for authorization; no test for 403/insufficient-permission scenarios
recommendations: Add pagination tests to ensure correct paging, limits, and total counts for large result sets
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to verify SLA under bursty traffic
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) to validate client-side caching and freshness
Extend authorization tests to cover 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions and possibly token revocation scenarios
